-\frac{2 \;i\log(i^2)}{2} = \pi
-\frac{2 \;i\log(i^2)}{2} = -i \log(i^2) = -i (i \pi)\implies
-x\;(x y)=-x\;y\;x\implies
-i\;(i \pi) = -i\;i\;\pi = \pi  \implies
-i\;i = (-i^2) = (-(-1)) = 1
\;\Bbb C-\Bbb R_+\;
-\frac{2i\log i^2}2=-\frac{2i\log(-1)}2=-\frac{2i\left(\log 1+i\pi\right)}2=-\frac{-2\pi}{2}=\pi
